<h2>Why Time-Boxing Builds Focus Habits</h2>

<p>[PLACEHOLDER — Explain the core mechanism: by committing to a fixed duration upfront, you remove the continuous decision of "should I keep going or stop?" This eliminates a major source of decision fatigue. The constraint also creates a sense of urgency that helps the brain enter focus mode faster. Over time, the habit of starting a timer becomes a powerful focus trigger.]</p>

